### Discriminitive vs Generative Models:
Disciminative Models optimize the *conditional* likelihood:
$\hat{\theta}_{\text{disc}} = \arg\max_{\theta} P(Y\mid X; \theta) = \arg\max_{\theta} \frac{P(X\mid Y; \theta)P(Y; \theta)}{P(X; \theta)}$
Generative Models optimize the *joint* likelihood:
$\hat{\theta}_{\text{gen}} = \arg\max_{\theta} P(X, Y; \theta) = \arg\max_{\theta} P(X\mid Y; \theta) P(Y; \theta)$
